<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80B51377D6AFF6A3B21FE32" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80B51377D6AFF6A3B21FE32" blockId="11.[828,1437,190,629]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80B51377D6AFF6A3CF3FF32" bold="true" box="[828,946,190,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80B51377A1AFF6A3BF2FF32" box="[1100,1203,190,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="3.05">3.05 mm</quantity>
. Antennomeres 9–11 distinctly elongate and enlarged, lacking modification. Horn-like metaventral processes long and broad at apices. Protrochanter with blunt ventral projection, profemur roundly angulate at middle, protibia with distinct apical protuberance; mesotrochanter bluntly protuberant. Median lobe of aedeagus almost symmetric dorso-ventrally; parameres elongate and slender; endophallus composed of 13 sclerites. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80B51307D6AFE0A3B6AFEB2" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80B51307D6AFE0A3CD9FED2" blockId="11.[828,1437,190,629]" lastBlockId="12.[828,1437,190,725]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80B51377D6AFE0A3B42FE12" bold="true" box="[828,1027,478,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">
Description. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80B51377D9DFE0A3B42FE12" bold="true" box="[971,1027,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">Male</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80B51377A46FE0A3B22FE12" box="[1040,1123,478,501]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[151,182,2061,2080]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,888,2037]" captionTargetId="figure-315@9.[210,1377,885,2042]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 7. Dorsal habitus of Pselaphodes males. A – P. jendeki sp. nov.; B – P. nongfa sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037482" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037482/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80B51377AADFE0A3A1DFE12" box="[1275,1372,478,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="3.05">3.05 mm</quantity>
. Head slightly longer than wide, HL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80B51377A38FE2A3B8CFDF2" box="[1134,1229,510,533]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="0.61">0.61 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80B51377B53FE2A3A25FDF2" box="[1285,1380,510,533]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="0.58">0.58 mm</quantity>
; eyes prominent, each composed of about 38 facets. Antennomeres 2–8 similarly moniliform; antennomeres 9–10 each elongate, antennomere10 truncate at base and with round apex, together they forming distinct club (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307C06FF6A3DE4FF32" box="[592,677,190,213]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
), which lacks modification. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307F83FF0A3D62FF12" box="[469,547,222,245]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than wide, PL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307F52FF2A3E28FEF2" box="[260,361,254,277]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="0.62">0.62 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307FFFFF2A3D4CFEF2" box="[425,525,254,277]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="0.58">0.58 mm</quantity>
, with lateral margins slightly expanding and then narrowing anteriorly at apical third. Elytra much broader than long, EL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307C61FEEA3DD4FEB2" box="[567,661,318,341]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.80 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307C9CFEEA3F82FE92" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.10 mm</quantity>
; disc with linear microsculpture. Horn-like metaventral processes (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307F5DFEAA3E1CFE72" box="[267,349,382,405]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
) elongate, in lateral view broadened at apex. Protrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307F21FE4A3E8BFE52" box="[375,458,414,437]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
) with blunt ventral protuberance; profemur roundly protuberant at middle; protibia (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307EC9FE0A3FB1FE12" box="[159,240,478,501]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
) with large apical tubercle; mesotrochanter (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307C9BFE0A3FF5FDF2" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
) with roundly triangular ventral projection; mesofemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307EC9FDCA3FACFDD2" box="[159,237,542,565]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
), metatrochanter and metafemur (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307C1BFDCA3DDEFDD2" box="[589,671,542,565]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9G</figureCitation>
) simple. Abdomen broad at base and narrowed apically, AL 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307C9FFDEA3F82FD92" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="0.92">0.92 mm</quantity>
, AW 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307F52FD8A3E2BFD92" box="[260,362,606,629]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.12" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="1.12">1.12 mm</quantity>
. Sternite 7 (IX) (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307C7BFD8A3DC5FD92" box="[557,644,606,629]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9H</figureCitation>
) elongate, hemi-membranous. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="134396FEE80C51307FB7FDAA3D0EFD72" box="[481,591,638,661]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" captionTargetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" captionTargetId="figure-219@11.[298,1290,677,1985]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes nongfa sp. nov. A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, K; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Figs 9I–E</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307C0BFDAA3DFAFD72" box="[605,699,638,661]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.60 mm</quantity>
long, almost symmetric dorso-ventrally; median lobe broad at base and narrowing apicad; parameres each elongate and slender (right paramere); with two short preapical setae; endophallus composed of six short sclerites at base, five similar ones at middle, and two elongate sclerites on the left side.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF07DAF3E80B51377EC1F8003ACCF7FB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037486" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5037486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037486/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" startId="11.[151,182,2004,2023]" targetBox="[298,1289,677,1983]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80B51377EC1F8003ACCF7FB" blockId="11.[151,1437,2004,2076]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 9. Male diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80B51377F96F8003D2DF800" authority="Yin &amp; Li, 2021" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[448,620,2004,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nongfa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80B51377F96F8003D2DF800" box="[448,620,2004,2023]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">Pselaphodes nongfa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23FEB12E80B51377C27F8003DF2F800" box="[625,691,2004,2023]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–E – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (E) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, F, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, E; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in E.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80C51307D0CFEEA3B6AFEB2" blockId="12.[828,1437,190,725]" box="[858,1067,318,341]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307D0CFEEA3CF5FEB2" bold="true" box="[858,948,318,341]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307D0CFEEA3CECFEB2" bold="true" box="[858,941,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80C51307D6AFE8A3BE0FDB2" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80C51307D6AFE8A3BE0FDB2" blockId="12.[828,1437,190,725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307D6AFE8A3B5DFE92" bold="true" box="[828,1052,350,373]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80C51307D6AFEAA3BB0FE72" authority="Huang, Li &amp; Yin, 2018" authorityName="Huang, Li &amp; Yin" authorityYear="2018" box="[828,1265,382,405]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maolanensis">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307D6AFEAA3CA1FE72" box="[828,992,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">P. maolanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE9F78AE80C51307DBCFEAA3BB0FE72" author="Huang, Li &amp; Yin" box="[1002,1265,382,405]" firstAuthor="Huang" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" pagination="457 - 478" part="DA" refId="ref13053" refString="HUANG M. - C., LI L. - Z. &amp; YIN Z. - W. 2018 a: Eleven new species and a new country record of Pselaphodes (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Pselaphinae) from China, with a revised checklist of world species. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae DA (2): 457 - 478." title="Eleven new species and a new country record of Pselaphodes (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Pselaphinae) from China, with a revised checklist of world species" type="journal article" year="2018">Huang, Li &amp; Yin, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80C51307B6FFEAA3AD9FE72" box="[1337,1432,382,405]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80C51307D85FE4A3B52FE52" box="[979,1043,414,437]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">China</collectingCountry>
by sharing many external features. The male of these two species can be readily separated by relatively much more elongate antennomere 
<quantity id="4C80279EE80C51307B37FE0A3ADDFE12" box="[1377,1436,478,501]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
relation to antennomeres 9 and 11, the narrow apical half of the aedeagus, as well as the more complex structure of endophallus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80C51307DB6FDEA3B09FDB2" authority="Yin &amp; Li, 2021" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[992,1096,574,597]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nongfa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307DB6FDEA3CB1FDB2" box="[992,1008,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307DA8FDEA3B09FDB2" box="[1022,1096,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">nongfa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23FEB12E80C51307A18FDEA3BE0FDB2" box="[1102,1185,574,597]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80C51307D6AFD8A3C8FFD52" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80C51307D6AFD8A3C8FFD52" blockId="12.[828,1437,190,725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307D6AFD8A3C80FD92" bold="true" box="[828,961,606,629]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after its 
<typeStatus id="54C334D9E80C51307B3BFD8A3ADDFD92" box="[1389,1436,606,629]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
locality, Nong Fa Lake (Blue Lake). The name is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80C51307D6AFD6A3B30FD32" box="[828,1137,702,725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80C51307D6AFD6A3B30FD32" blockId="12.[828,1437,190,725]" box="[828,1137,702,725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80C51307D6AFD6A3C8FFD32" bold="true" box="[828,974,702,725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80C51307D82FD6A3B4DFD32" box="[980,1036,702,725]" name="Laos" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Laos</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80C51307A43FD6A3B2CFD32" box="[1045,1133,702,725]" country="Laos" name="Attapu" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Attapeu</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
